to Athena and her family

39:55.427 --> 39:58.096
for a lifetime
of happiness, love

39:58.129 --> 40:00.098
and all the home-cooked meals
you can eat.

40:00.131 --> 40:01.767
Oh, that's sweet.

40:01.800 --> 40:04.436
But let's not forget
it's also a big damn diamond.

40:04.470 --> 40:06.237
(laughter)

40:06.271 --> 40:07.939
-(doorbell rings)
-You got that?

40:07.973 --> 40:09.775
-Yeah.
-All right.

40:09.808 --> 40:11.910
-Merry Christmas.
-Ah. Thanks for inviting me.

40:11.943 --> 40:15.447
I brought Christmas, and...
I brought congratulations.

40:15.481 --> 40:17.783
Ah, thank you.
Well, you are always welcome.

40:17.816 --> 40:19.818
Maddie didn't want to join us?

40:19.851 --> 40:22.888
I think this year she needed
a different kind of Christmas.

40:22.921 --> 40:25.857
-All right, well, come on in.
-All right. I'm excited.

40:30.161 --> 40:31.563
(knocking)

40:31.597 --> 40:35.233
Behold, I bring you
good tidings of great joy.

40:35.266 --> 40:37.335
Chinese food and Die Hard,

40:37.368 --> 40:39.638
the greatest
Christmas movie ever made.

40:39.671 --> 40:41.139
I'm sorry.

40:41.172 --> 40:43.609
-About the tree. I shouldn't...
-Whoa-ho-ho.

40:43.642 --> 40:46.612
Christmas is supposed to be
about feeling safe and warm

40:46.645 --> 40:49.748
with the people you care about;
that's the gift.

40:49.781 --> 40:51.917
What it's wrapped in
doesn't matter.

40:51.950 --> 40:53.752
Who needs a tree?

